Cowton railway station is a disused station on the East Coast Main Line, it is situated in the Hambleton district of North Yorkshire in England the station is situated around 0.5 miles (0.8km) east of the village of East Cowton. Several of the railway buildings have survived the closure of the station and are now used as residential properties.  
